result.name: Sheung Hei

reviews.text: All time favourite for Cantonese dishes as they never fail to maintain the quality. Their fried crabs are so nice but you have to bring your own seafood. Their chef is good at handling seafood although they are not written on the menu! I can't recommend one favourite dish as so so many dishes are so yummy. Particularly famous for the cantonese pot rice 煲仔飯 with cured pork sausage and meat they smell so good when they open the lid when the steam comes out with the aroma of rice and cured meat, they are just perfect match. Not to mention any Chinese dishes you can name, they make the most mainstream dishes to another level. Make sure you visit to get the real taste and local taste of Cantonese cuisine!

Food is great and the variety really blows your mind. Only draw back for the uninitiated is the service. To be very honest, it's not all that bad but its hard to get an acknowledgement. If you are up to it, do give this establishment a shot...the food really speaks for itself.

Okay clay pot for a fairly high price. The crispy rice at the bottom was really good. Okay portion sizes. English menu if requested. Very busy during peak hours but fast service. Friendly staff. Free tea.
Great dim sum, great variety and good price. The only down part is that they messed our order up twice but we will be coming back.

Keep the dishes in traditional Hong Kong Canton styles. Provide a vast variety of choices. Also, delicious and local dim sum can be ordered. They are ordered to steam. Keep the freshness and hotness. 
The price is reasonably marked.
Many people queue in peak hours. It is expected to wait for 1 hour without reservation. It worths the queue.
Excellent representative of Hong Kong cuisine!!!!@

reviews.text: The best! A rare classic dim sum/ classic clay pot dishes restaurant, where the prices and portion does not aim to rip you off. I hope it stays this way. Dinner is till 10/ 10:15 PM but after you can have dim sum all night it's 24 hours. Never disappoints. Love this place.
A very nice dim-sum restaurant opens round the clock.

We went to the Clay Pot Restaurant.  It was busy as usual but we managed to get a table just ahead of the peak time, Had Black vinegar fish, Sizzling chicken hot pot, Spare rib clay pot rice and Eel and frog clay pot rice.  The food was excellent as usual. Service is typical Chinese style and was good.  Well worth the visit and a little bit of wait time if needed.
Well known Canton food here
Food nice and prices reasonable !

result.adr_address: 香港西環北街25號
result.name: 嚐囍煲仔小菜

reviews.text: 好吃•但排很久•早到較妥
是一間米茲蓮中式飯店，馳名煲仔飯，點心，小菜，通宵營業，味道相當好，服務員只有幾個，但服務態度很好，價格相宜，免加一服務費，茶價3元至5元不等，看時段，下午2:OO至6:OO免茶，食得開心，可一試再試。大約有2O張枱左右，两人位偏多，需長期等位，最好先去訂位然後行街。附近堅尼地城地鐵站，舖位林立，交通方便。

一間煲仔飯出名，每次去食都要排隊，而最近嗰次，直頭走人無得食，因客人太多，等候時間太耐，其實，除煲仔飯外，亦有小菜選擇，如大家想試試的話，建議大家下午6点前光顧，因普遍晚膳時間，由6点半至8点半左右，所以嗰段時間人流會小D，價錢合理，服務可以好少少，可以理解，客太多待應不夠，眼見D待應做到唔停手，而光顧的客人，都是來自本地香港人為多，對此舖位置不夠熟，大家可乘九巴(904)，電車往堅尼地城，港鐵係堅尼地城站出
老師父美食，現在很難食到懷舊味。贊贊贊！！

我一個人來看到排隊人龍心想不妙，結果我完全不用等待就直接被叫進去了哈哈哈哈，裡頭會有大圓桌很多組客人一起坐。

漫長等待是在點餐之後，因為最裡面手機網路訊號很差，所以可能只能乾等了～

親自品嚐看看才知道啦，我沒有失望但也不到特別驚艷，不過有吃過才沒有留下遺憾。
